content: .@HawleyMO tells @FOX2now the state was slated to have 350,00 doses of the #CovidVaccine by the end of Dec., but with the delay of the #PfizerBioNTech vaccine, #Missouri will now only receive around 300,000 doses. He says #MO is still on track to have 2M doses by Feb. #moleg
date: 4:44 AM · Dec 18, 2020 from Missouri, USA·Twitter for iPhone
